🔁 Day 27 – OOP + CLI + Argument Parsing Revision




🔹 1. Course Registration Tool 
Create a script course_reg.py with:
Class Student with name, roll, course
Accept values via command-line args: --name, --roll, --course
Print:
Student [name] (Roll: [roll]) has registered for [course]



🔹 2. Rectangle Calculator
Create rectangle_tool.py using:
Rectangle class: takes length and width
Accept --length and --width via CLI
Add method to compute and print area and perimeter



🔹 3. Student Score Evaluator 
Create score_eval.py:
Accept a file path via --file (text file containing names and marks)
Read the file line by line (Name, Score)
Print only students with score ≥ 60

📝 Use a sample file like:

Ravi, 70  
Amit, 45  
Sana, 90  




🔹 4. Password Analyzer Tool 
Create pass_check.py:
Class Password with value as input
Methods:
is_strong() → length ≥ 8, mix of letters + digits
show_strength() → print result
Use --password as input from terminal.




🔹 5. Weather Bot  
Create weather_bot.py:
WeatherBot class with city as attribute
Use CLI input --city
Print mock weather based on city:
Use dictionary inside the class for random mappings:
Delhi → “Hot”
Shimla → “Cold”
Mumbai → “Humid”
